If your interest is developing extra functionality, and you don&#39;t have 
to use Heritrix 1.14.x for historic/project reasons, I suggest using 
recent Heritrix 3.x code as the basis. It&#39;s easier to hook in custom 
functionality.

Still, in H1 or H3, there should be a log or directory (perhaps under 
/tmp for linux) with more information about the test failures, including 
the exact test method that failed and a code stack pinpointing the 
failure. That would make what&#39;s going wrong for your builds more clear.

- Gordon @ IA


